snippet.textDisplay:
How was the call at 3:20 holding?

He was stopping the defence from getting past thus providing the Quarterback more time to pass the ball.

In fact I don't understand half the holding calls on the NFL.

What I would consider holding would be if one player was literally holding another player on the ground preventing them from getting up not stopping a player from advancing.

Whats the point in having a pocket if the players that have created not being allowed to do anything to prevent the opposing team from getting by.

The NFL isn't a game played by preschoolers, it's a game played by adults so they should start treating it ad such.

snippet.textDisplay: I don’t know why you even posted this. Eli Manning was the only one that played football in that game with the exceptions of Darius Slayton and Marcus Golden, but the loss is going to be blamed on him. The giants have to be one of the worst teams that has ever been seen in the past 30 years. And as a giants fan, the coaching, o-line, and entire defense besides maybe 3-4 people need to be cut and upgraded. I mean, Eli Manning has the ball for most of the first half, and he dominates, 17-3. In the second half, he barely touches the ball, because of the god-awful defense, and when he does, he’s getting sacked every damn play. The second half performance was just pathetic, the coaching is nothing more than miserable, and I don’t know why I thought we had a chance of winning tonight.
